{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"set","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"returnOnCancel"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"returnOnCancel"},{"text":" is ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"text":", then cancelling ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"task"},{"text":"‘s","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Cancellable","isActive":true},{"text":" will immediately cause it to return, as though the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"task’s "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TaskThreadFunc","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" had called"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_task_return_error_if_cancelled()"},{"text":" and then returned.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This allows you to create a cancellable wrapper around an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"uninterruptible function. The "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TaskThreadFunc","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" just needs to be"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"careful that it does not modify any externally-visible state after","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"it has been cancelled. To do that, the thread should call"},{"text":" ","typ